title: Dilution
alt: Dear editors of Homeopathy Monthly: I have two small corrections for your July issue. One, it's spelled "echinacea", and two, homeopathic medicines are no better than placebos and your entire magazine is a sham.
transcript:
[Cueball stands at a desk with a beaker in one hand and a turkey baster in the other. Megan lies in a bed in the same room.]Cueball: Okay, this time I've diluted the semen 30x.
Megan: We'll be sure to get pregnant now!Belief in homeopathy is not, evolutionarily, selected for.
